children.subject: Have you tried emailing the EE 120 professor? Her email is avz@eecs.berkeley.edu.

history.content:
Please note you always want to enroll into the class that does not allow the time conflict first. Then enroll into the class that allows the time conflict. 

Because both of these classes are set up in the system to not allow time conflict you will need to contact the EE enrollment manager to process the time conflict override for EE 120 IF the instructor approves of the time conflict. You will need to forward the confirmation email from the instructor to ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu We can only process the override if there are open seats in the class and the instructor approves.

Hello,

I'd like to take CS 61C, EE 120, and EECS 149 this upcoming fall but I noticed that all of these classes conflict with one another. I've emailed and got confirmation that EECS 149 will not allow time conflicts. I've tried emailing but did not receive an answer on if EE 120 allows for time conflicts this fall.

Could someone help me figure out if this is a possible schedule considering the time conflicts? Thank you!
history.subject: Fall 2021 EE 120 & EECS 149 Time Conflicts
